          {
            "commit": "a8e14f78611ecc0ff3da73e603816d4f58e274de",
            "subject": "LU-6027 osd-zfs: Preserve lu_buf when listing EAs"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Li Wei",
          "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-11-28 09:15:04.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Li Wei",
          "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-01-04 01:00:38.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6027 mdd: Don't list \"trusted.link\" for orphans",
        "message": "LU-6027 mdd: Don't list \"trusted.link\" for orphans\n\nCommit 09fe679 prevents mdd_xattr_get() from accessing XATTR_NAME_LINK\nEAs of orphan objects but leaves mdd_xattr_list() unchanged.  This is\nproblematic for fgetxattr() calls on orphan objects when EA cache\nrefills are involved.  To respond to such a refill, mdt lists all of\nthe object's EA names and gets the value for each name.  In the case\nof an orphan, XATTR_NAME_LINK EA will be listed, but corresponding\nmdd_xattr_get() call will return -ENOENT, causing the fgetxattr() call\nto fail eventually.  This patch updates mdd_xattr_list() to filter out\nXATTR_NAME_LINK EAs for orphan objects as well, following commit\n09fe679.\n\nChange-Id: I1546fe167e67e48e094b467641e73b4bbd5c3625\nSigned-off-by: Li Wei <wei.g.li@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_5"
    }
  },
